    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180\u00b0C/ 160\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 4, then boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced red onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lentil-and-roasted-courgette-ragu-and-wholemeal-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s] </strong>in half lengthways, then slice into half moons</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lentil-and-roasted-courgette-ragu-and-wholemeal-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>green lentils</strong> to the onion and cook for 3-4 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lentil-and-roasted-courgette-ragu-and-wholemeal-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lentil-and-roasted-courgette-ragu-and-wholemeal-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-10 min or until the sauce has thickened to a bolognese sauce-like consistency \u2013 this is your<strong> lentil rag\u00f9</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lentil-and-roasted-courgette-ragu-and-wholemeal-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta </strong>and reserve a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lentil-and-roasted-courgette-ragu-and-wholemeal-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>courgette</strong> to the<strong> </strong>lentil rag\u00f9 and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry!</p><p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> Tuscan-style lentil & roasted courgette rag\u00f9</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lentil-and-roasted-courgette-ragu-and-wholemeal-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>to the pan with the <strong>Tuscan-style lentil & roasted courgette rag\u00f9</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped basil</strong> and your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
